org.eclipse.eef

Interface EEFPageDescription

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EEFPageDescriptionImpl

    public interface EEFPageDescription
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'EEF Page Description'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Identifier
    • Label Expression
    • Domain Class
    • Semantic Candidate Expression
    • Precondition Expression
    • Groups
    • Semantic Validation Rules
    • Indented
    • Actions
    See Also:
    EefPackage.getEEFPageDescription()

      • getGroups

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<EEFGroupDescription> getGroups()
        Returns the value of the 'Groups' reference list. The list contents are of type EEFGroupDescription. References the Groups which are visible in a Page. If not specified, the EEF runtime looks for all the Groups defined under the View containing the Page that have a domainClass which is equal or a super class of the domainClass of the Page and use them following the order of the inheritance tree of the EObject.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Groups' reference list.
        See Also:
        EefPackage.getEEFPageDescription_Groups()
